ath.\n    - strong: Merge criteria\n    - list:\n      - listitem: Schema fields, capability states, and tuple hash inputs must remain byte-compatible with 279.\n      - listitem: Binding compilation must name exactly one current adapter profile, degradation profile, and confirmation gate policy.\n      - listitem: Capability tuple supersession must invalidate stale resolutions without widening patient action scope.\n      - listitem: Blocked reasons and fallback actions must remain machine-readable for downstream UI and support tracks.\n      - listitem: Telemetry and diagnostics must stay PHI-safe and reason-code based.\n    - strong: Mandatory tests\n    - list:\n      - listitem: pnpm --dir /Users/test/Code/V/packages/domains/booking typecheck\n      - listitem: pnpm --dir /Users/test/Code/V/services/command-api typecheck\n      - listitem: pnpm --dir /Users/test/Code/V/packages/domains/booking exec vitest run tests/phase4-booking-capability-engine.test.ts\n      - listitem: pnpm --dir /Users/test/Code/V/services/command-api exec vitest run tests/phase4-booking-capability.integration.test.js\n      - listitem: python3 /Users/test/Code/V/tools/analysis/validate_283_capability_engine.py\n    - strong: Launch packet\n    - list:\n      - listitem: \"Objective: Implement the executable capability matrix compiler and tuple resolution engine without re-owning BookingCase semantics or slot/commit truth.\"\n      - listitem: \"Forbidden shortcuts: Do not mutate BookingCase.status or SearchPolicy semantics in 283.; Do not infer slot, reservation, confirmation, or waitlist truth from capability alone.; Do not widen patient action scope beyond BookingCapabilityProjection.; Do not let more than one binding or policy seam be current for a legal tuple.\"\n      - listitem: \"Fail closed: Ambiguous matrix row or binding compilation fails blocked, not partial.; Publication, trust, linkage, or governing-object drift supersedes stale capability resolutions.; Any attempt to render